paper_abstract: A topological index of a molecular graph G is a numeric quantity related to G that is invariant under symmetry properties of G. A dendrimer is an artificially manufactured or synthesized molecule built up from branched units called monomers. In this paper the Wiener, PI, vertex PI, the first and second Zagreb indices of a class of nanostar dendrimer are computed.
paper_title: The Wiener, Szeged, PI, vertex PI, the First and Second Zagreb Indices of N-branched Phenylacetylenes Dendrimers
